[normal]7.[bold]              [bold]The interaction between mental health conditions and [bold]LTCs[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]7.1
[normal]              
[normal]The BAD 
[normal]recognises
[normal] 
[normal]the strong inter-relationship of mental health conditions with long-term physical health conditions
[normal],
[normal] and particularly with skin conditions 
[normal]that
[normal] are often both disabling and disfiguring. It is also 
[normal]important to acknowledge that patients may present with a skin condition which masks an underlying, untreated mental health problem. The recent BAD 
[normal]document
[normal] 
[normal]‘W
[normal]orking 
[normal]P
[normal]arty
[normal] R
[normal]eport
[normal] 
[normal]on
[normal] M
[normal]inimum
[normal] S
[normal]tandards
[normal] 
[normal]for
[normal] P
[normal]sycho
[normal]-
[normal]Dermatology
[normal] S
[normal]ervices 
[normal]2012’
[normal] 
[normal]outlines key information on psychosocial support service delivery requirements. The report 
[normal]delineates
[normal] minimum service standards for psychosocial support.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7.2
[normal]              
[normal]The BAD has also recently been awarded
[normal],
[normal] a Department of Health 
